summary: What I liked about Gendry’s failed proposal in 8.04 is the way it perfectly matches with the theme song of Arya x Gendry, My...
body:
What I liked about Gendry’s failed proposal in 8.04 is the way it perfectly matches with the theme song of Arya x Gendry, My Featherbed. Like, Gendry runs to Arya right after being legitimised and asks her to be his lady, completely forgetting that she doesn’t want to be a lady and they’ve been dating for like two days, and really, he’s lucky he’s so cute, this poor fool.

My featherbed is deep and soft,
and there I’ll lay you down,
I’ll dress you all in yellow silk,
and on your head a crown.
For you shall be my lady love,
and I shall be your lord.
I’ll always keep you warm and safe,
and guard you with my sword.

And obviously, Arya freaks out, and all her insecurities and old fears planted into her head by a patriarchal society immediately strike again and lead to drastic decisions. And maybe there is also a big chunk of confusion and lost propose after defeating the Final Boss when she didn’t even expect to survive, which doesn’t help either.

And how she smiled and how she laughed,
the maiden of the tree.
She spun away and said to him,
no featherbed for me.

The sad part is that neither Arya nor Gendry has enough experience to handle this situation differently (remember, Gendry is just five or six years older than Arya). And while they both feel that a woman doesn’t have to choose between different sides of herself, they don’t have examples of this in front of them and don’t know how to articulate this idea.

I’ll wear a gown of golden leaves,
and bind my hair with grass,
But you can be my forest love,
and me your forest lass.

Ironically, if Gendry waited just one day to make his move or if Arya didn’t run away to King’s Landing, Brienne could’ve become that example. Alas, now they have to learn the hard way and figure everything out by themselves. They are good kids, though, and I believe in them.

summary: Arya reunited with Gendry, flirted, admired him from afar, chose him as her first time, was called beautiful, told "I love you"...
body:
Arya reunited with Gendry, flirted, admired him from afar, chose him as her first time, was called beautiful, told “I love you” and then received a proposal, all in a matter of days.

At 18 years old.

Her arc since S1 has been about her list. Her arc in s8 is about returning to herself but she can’t, not fully, until her list is finished. Once that’s done the next chapter of her life can begin. Even if that involves sailing across the world, the bond she has with Gendry, particularly now, is stronger than it has ever been. She’ll be the one that got away and he’ll be the boy who loved her. And once she’s healed, particularly after being on her own for a while, she’ll start to see it for what it is.

Maybe I’ve read too many Gendry fics but this is how so many of them start - with Arya’s return from across the sea and a particular bull-headed Baratheon on her mind. If she needs time away to figure out what she wants I’m in, but I also know Gendry will open his arms upon her return. We all would for the one who got away; more so if they were our first love.

summary: Something I wish D&D would understand is that just because you were a tomboy who thought anything feminine was icky at 11 years...
body: Something I wish D&D would understand is that just because you were a tomboy who thought anything feminine was icky at 11 years old does not mean that for the rest of your life you’re incapable of changing. What I wanted to be at 11 is so completely different from what I want to be now. The idea that Arya can’t find happiness and love with Gendry because she’s “not a lady” is so stupid because it’s saying she’s still the same person with the same goals that she had as a child. Also she doesn’t have to give up who she is to be a traditional Lady. It doesn’t have to be one or the other. Let Arya change and grow as a person. Let her be happy you cowards.

summary: My formal petition of this weekend is..
body:
My formal petition of this weekend is..

As the Last to weeks, I’m doing a post for my favorite character to survive…Please please don’t let Arya either die or leave by herself out of westeros.

She truly deserves to be happy, even more than before, she loves her family, she loves Gendry, and yeah, she Still needs to revenge her father, Mother and brothers but mostly she deserves Happiness.

So, please please, this be a good, happy, no dying episode.
